column5: The family and I spent last week up at a resort on Rice Lake.  The fishing was excellent.    I'll let Mistyjr post his own pics as he had a pretty darn good week as well.   Here's some pics.....            I limited out in Walleye one morning with one 20 incher and three between 16 to 18 inches.  My partner for the morning caught two as well.        Saw tons of dead carp...hit a couple by accident as well.    A couple of Ben in action....   Double header...micro tube and worm...   I ended up with 15 Bass for the week..all between 14 to 16 inches.  All were released.    The Lew Catfish   ...   The mid-week fish fry....   Our dog enjoying the boat...   Nice shot by my wife...   The family shot
Nice report... that a pretty stringer of 'o fish.
Great report Misty1, I must say, I miss fishing Rice Lake, big time.  Judging by the stringer of eyes, you got the tehnique down there.  What resort did you guys stay at?
Excellent report and Pics Misty its good to see a report from you again.  MTP
Great report, pics, and fish Jim!!!  Good lookin' family shot too!!!
awesome report, looks like you guys had a great time  cheers!
Looks like you had a good outing for sure, nice haul...
Great report, looks like you had a super week.  Thanks for the report.
Thanks for sharing your vacation.....it's always nice to get away with the family for some r&r and great times!!
Great report Jim. Congrats on a successful family outing.  Mike
Great Report! Sounds like it was a very successful vacation. What were the pickerel biting on?
Thanks for the replies guys.  Hooked - We stayed at Shady Acres.  Johnny - Worm harnesses.
WTG Jim and crew! The smiles say it all! Thanks, HH
WOW! Great report... man the walleye are on fire on rice this year.. GOOD JOB!
Thats a great family report, thanks.  Beautiful heron shot too - is it just me or do they seem to be all over the place this year?  I don't recall seeing nearly as many last year.
